description: Deletes an Amazon File Cache resource. After deletion, the cache no longer exists, and its data is gone. The DeleteFileCache operation returns while the cache has the DELETING status. You can check the cache deletion status by calling the DescribeFileCaches operation, which returns a list of caches in your account. If you pass the cache ID for a deleted cache, the DescribeFileCaches operation returns a FileCacheNotFound error.

parameters.name: FileCacheId
parameters.description: The ID of the cache that's being deleted.

parameters.name: ClientRequestToken
parameters.description: (Optional) An idempotency token for resource creation, in a string of up to 63 ASCII characters. This token is automatically filled on your behalf when you use the Command Line Interface (CLI) or an Amazon Web Services SDK. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: FileCacheId
nested_items.description: The ID of the cache that's being deleted.

nested_items.name: Lifecycle
nested_items.description: The cache lifecycle for the deletion request. If the DeleteFileCache operation is successful, this status is DELETING.
